1
00:00:57,348 --> 00:01:01,978
TASTEFULLY YOURS

2
00:01:02,062 --> 00:01:04,147
I forget it all the time.

3
00:01:04,230 --> 00:01:05,065
Oh my gosh!

4
00:01:05,148 --> 00:01:07,233
Mo Yeon-joo! Where are you going?

5
00:01:07,317 --> 00:01:09,360
What's the matter with you?

6
00:01:09,444 --> 00:01:11,237
What is it? Is something wrong?

7
00:01:11,321 --> 00:01:13,823
Why are you running
all over the place this morning?

8
00:01:16,367 --> 00:01:18,244
No, nothing's wrong.

9
00:01:18,328 --> 00:01:20,288
What are you stuttering for?

10
00:01:20,371 --> 00:01:21,456
I didn't.

11
00:01:21,539 --> 00:01:25,543
-When did I stutter…
-Whatever. Be quiet.

12
00:01:25,627 --> 00:01:28,129
We're going grocery shopping,
so watch the restaurant.

13
00:01:28,213 --> 00:01:29,214
Clean up as well.

14
00:01:29,297 --> 00:01:31,007
-You're going out?
-Get a grip.

15
00:01:31,591 --> 00:01:32,425
See you later!

16
00:01:33,593 --> 00:01:35,887
Don't be gone for too long.
I'll be lonely.

17
00:01:41,643 --> 00:01:44,187
The recipe book.

18
00:01:44,270 --> 00:01:46,523
The recipes. Damn it.

19
00:01:49,442 --> 00:01:50,360
The recipe book.

20
00:01:50,443 --> 00:01:52,195
Goddammit.

21
00:01:58,451 --> 00:01:59,285
What the…

22
00:02:05,375 --> 00:02:06,334
No way.

23
00:02:07,585 --> 00:02:10,588
LAST NIGHT

24
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:31,901
He always went on and on about
high-end and premium,

25
00:02:32,819 --> 00:02:34,237
and this is where he works?

26
00:02:35,738 --> 00:02:36,990
By the way, Yu-jin.

27
00:02:37,991 --> 00:02:39,242
Why do you go so far

28
00:02:40,034 --> 00:02:42,954
as to risk everything
to get those three stars?

29
00:02:43,538 --> 00:02:44,831
What do you mean?

30
00:02:45,498 --> 00:02:50,295
I do this because my honor
and pride depend on it.

31
00:02:50,378 --> 00:02:53,298
I do it because my salary
and career path depend on it.

32
00:02:53,798 --> 00:02:56,885
I'll mention the three stars on my resume,
get a new job, and get a raise.

33
00:02:57,719 --> 00:02:58,720
Get a new job?

34
00:02:59,596 --> 00:03:01,806
Didn't you get into Hansang
through open recruitment?

35
00:03:01,890 --> 00:03:03,558
It doesn't matter how I got in.

36
00:03:03,641 --> 00:03:05,977
No one stays at one job
for their whole life.

37
00:03:06,477 --> 00:03:08,271
You jump ship if you're offered a raise.

38
00:03:08,897 --> 00:03:10,398
Come on. Help me find it.

39
00:03:34,589 --> 00:03:35,590
I found them.

40
00:03:36,466 --> 00:03:37,717
What?

41
00:03:41,012 --> 00:03:42,513
The recipes Director Han mentioned.

42
00:03:44,349 --> 00:03:47,227
Money, honor, pride.

43
00:03:48,895 --> 00:03:49,896
I found them.

44
00:03:54,484 --> 00:03:56,527
-This has to be thinner.
-Yes, Chef.

45
00:03:56,611 --> 00:03:57,737
-Step aside.
-Yes, Chef.

46
00:03:59,948 --> 00:04:02,158
-Keep it this thin, okay?
-Yes, Chef.

47
00:04:02,242 --> 00:04:04,369
-Let me have a taste test.
-Yes, Chef.

48
00:04:07,413 --> 00:04:09,290
-It needs more black pepper.
-Yes, Chef.

49
00:04:12,502 --> 00:04:15,922
HAN BEOM-WOO

50
00:04:16,005 --> 00:04:16,965
CHEF JANG YOUNG-HYE

51
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:21,469
Come on, pick up.

52
00:04:21,552 --> 00:04:24,097
Pick up the phone.

53
00:04:24,180 --> 00:04:26,599
BROTHER'S VEGETABLE SHOP

54
00:04:28,226 --> 00:04:32,897
This was made with 200-year-old
aged soy sauce from North Jeolla Province.

55
00:04:32,981 --> 00:04:34,023
Noted.

56
00:04:36,150 --> 00:04:38,486
All right, everyone. You can do this!

57
00:04:40,613 --> 00:04:42,573
HAN BEOM-WOO

58
00:04:45,076 --> 00:04:47,829
They're Diamant inspectors, so stay sharp.

59
00:04:47,912 --> 00:04:49,247
-Yes, Chef.
-Yes, Chef.

60
00:04:54,377 --> 00:04:56,004
Damn you, Jang Young-hye!

61
00:05:13,146 --> 00:05:15,064
This is grilled red tilefish with scales

62
00:05:15,148 --> 00:05:17,108
served on top of a soy sauce
scaly hedgehog mushroom purée

63
00:05:17,191 --> 00:05:19,527
with Korean mint and spinach oil.

64
00:05:19,610 --> 00:05:20,695
I hope you enjoy it.

65
00:05:29,954 --> 00:05:31,539
-Two more pinches of salt.
-Yes, Chef.

66
00:05:37,420 --> 00:05:38,755
Fire the next course.

67
00:05:38,838 --> 00:05:40,256
-Yes, Chef.
-Yes, Chef.

68
00:05:41,591 --> 00:05:43,342
You must follow the recipe exactly.

69
00:05:43,426 --> 00:05:44,302
-Yes, Chef.
-Yes, Chef.

70
00:05:45,970 --> 00:05:46,846
HOW TO GRILL PINE MUSHROOM

71
00:05:46,929 --> 00:05:48,347
ADD MINCED BEEF RUMP AND MIX
CUT SEOPSANJEOK INTO A SQUARE

72
00:05:50,808 --> 00:05:52,435
-Step aside.
-Yes, Chef.

73
00:06:31,057 --> 00:06:32,183
Damn it.

74
00:06:39,273 --> 00:06:40,108
Wait.

75
00:06:45,321 --> 00:06:46,989
Goodbye. Thank you.

76
00:07:02,338 --> 00:07:06,425
TASTEFULLY YOURS

77
00:07:07,510 --> 00:07:09,887
1 HOUR AGO

78
00:07:14,058 --> 00:07:16,936
This is seopsanjeok,
infused with a wild pine mushroom aroma.

79
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:40,626
Hey, Jang Young-hye. Follow me.

80
00:07:43,421 --> 00:07:44,297
Hey.

81
00:07:48,593 --> 00:07:49,510
Don't you think…

82
00:07:50,470 --> 00:07:52,722
Don't you think that's just wrong?

83
00:07:52,805 --> 00:07:54,682
It's the trick you came up with
and taught me.

84
00:07:54,765 --> 00:07:57,143
It's what you do best.

85
00:07:57,226 --> 00:07:59,103
I know that.

86
00:08:00,521 --> 00:08:01,355
You're right, but--

87
00:08:01,439 --> 00:08:05,276
You can change your ways
because you won't lose it all right away.

88
00:08:05,359 --> 00:08:07,778
You can switch sides whenever you want
and do as you wish.

89
00:08:07,862 --> 00:08:09,197
But

90
00:08:09,780 --> 00:08:12,783
did you ever stop to think about Yu-jin
and the other chefs who work for us?

91
00:08:12,867 --> 00:08:16,037
Did you even consider
the people who worked with you?

92
00:08:19,290 --> 00:08:21,083
Get a grip, Han Beom-woo.

93
00:08:21,667 --> 00:08:24,962
This is your workplace,
not that restaurant.

94
00:08:25,671 --> 00:08:27,131
So wrap things up there.

95
00:08:27,715 --> 00:08:29,675
Our three-star menu has to be exclusive.

96
00:08:29,759 --> 00:08:32,637
It can't be a menu people can have
at another restaurant.

97
00:08:37,308 --> 00:08:39,268
You'd better wrap things up quickly.

98
00:08:53,866 --> 00:08:55,326
Goddammit.

99
00:08:58,955 --> 00:09:03,084
I'M NOT FEELING WELL DUE TO JET LAG,
SO I'LL BE TAKING THE DAY OFF, CHEF

100
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:04,544
Jet lag? We were in Japan.

101
00:09:29,485 --> 00:09:31,529
What's up with you two?

102
00:09:31,612 --> 00:09:36,242
Hey, Chef, did you hear that rumor?

103
00:09:37,159 --> 00:09:38,369
What rumor?

104
00:09:38,452 --> 00:09:40,746
Some shameless fool from the area

105
00:09:41,539 --> 00:09:44,292
drank all day long, fooled around,
and skipped work without permission.

106
00:09:44,375 --> 00:09:45,835
As if that wasn't bad enough,
the very next day,

107
00:09:45,918 --> 00:09:50,506
he showed his thick face
as if nothing had happened.

108
00:09:51,674 --> 00:09:53,426
Because of him,

109
00:09:53,509 --> 00:09:56,512
a poor woman named Jin Myung-sook

110
00:09:56,596 --> 00:10:00,725
ended up with housewife's eczema

111
00:10:02,101 --> 00:10:03,561
that she'd never had in her 40-year life.

112
00:10:03,644 --> 00:10:05,313
All because she had to do
the damn fool's chores too.

113
00:10:05,396 --> 00:10:06,939
The what fool? The "damn" fool?

114
00:10:07,023 --> 00:10:09,859
Oh, are you upset?
I wasn't talking about you.

115
00:10:09,942 --> 00:10:11,652
Who said I got drunk and fooled around?

116
00:10:11,736 --> 00:10:15,114
-Who on earth said that?
-Oh goodness, I wasn't talking about you.

117
00:10:15,197 --> 00:10:16,782
Gosh, he's funny, isn't he?

118
00:10:16,866 --> 00:10:18,826
Do you know that I returned
after sacrificing myself

119
00:10:18,909 --> 00:10:20,453
for the greater good?

120
00:10:20,536 --> 00:10:22,413
You don't even know anything.

121
00:10:22,496 --> 00:10:23,956
"The greater good"?

122
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:26,250
Since when did drinking and fooling around
count as the greater good?

123
00:10:26,334 --> 00:10:28,628
-I've never heard of such a thing, Chef.
-Chef Mo.

124
00:10:28,711 --> 00:10:30,838
Have you heard that rumor?

125
00:10:30,921 --> 00:10:33,007
Someone acted like she'd follow
Yu-jin or whatever his name is

126
00:10:33,090 --> 00:10:34,884
to the ends of hell,

127
00:10:34,967 --> 00:10:36,886
only to keep coming back here.

128
00:10:37,678 --> 00:10:39,764
Oh, I get it. It's not that she didn't go.

129
00:10:39,847 --> 00:10:41,974
She couldn't go because she was rejected.

130
00:10:44,226 --> 00:10:45,269
For goodness' sake.

131
00:10:47,271 --> 00:10:49,857
You hit me? Did you just hit me?

132
00:10:49,940 --> 00:10:52,109
Yeah, I hit you!

133
00:10:52,985 --> 00:10:54,111
Stop it.

134
00:11:12,254 --> 00:11:14,632
You think you can get away
with this attitude?

135
00:11:18,511 --> 00:11:19,845
How dare he.

136
00:11:32,733 --> 00:11:35,152
You should apologize to her first.

137
00:11:35,820 --> 00:11:36,987
Why should I?

138
00:11:37,905 --> 00:11:40,032
I'm the one who got beat up
and was wronged,

139
00:11:40,116 --> 00:11:41,075
so why should I apologize?

140
00:11:41,158 --> 00:11:42,952
That happens.

141
00:11:43,035 --> 00:11:44,161
All right?

142
00:11:44,245 --> 00:11:46,997
Do what's best for everyone and let it go.

143
00:11:47,081 --> 00:11:49,250
What am I, everyone's whipping boy?

144
00:11:49,333 --> 00:11:51,043
That goes for Myung-sook
and Beom-woo's ex-girlfriend too.

145
00:11:51,127 --> 00:11:52,711
They're all hounding me.

146
00:11:53,838 --> 00:11:54,880
His ex-girlfriend?

147
00:11:54,964 --> 00:11:55,798
Yeah.

148
00:11:55,881 --> 00:11:58,008
I said I sacrificed myself.

149
00:11:58,092 --> 00:12:00,469
You know
what Beom-woo's ex-girlfriend did?

150
00:12:00,553 --> 00:12:03,681
She kicked my behind
with killer high heels.

151
00:12:03,764 --> 00:12:05,433
I bet she left a hole in my butt cheek.

152
00:12:05,516 --> 00:12:06,517
Why did she come back?

153
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:09,061
That's not what's important right now.

154
00:12:09,145 --> 00:12:10,771
My sacrifice is important, okay?

155
00:12:11,355 --> 00:12:13,899
Chef. You're on my side, right?

156
00:12:20,823 --> 00:12:23,576
BROTHER'S VEGETABLE SHOP

157
00:13:10,998 --> 00:13:11,916
YU-JIN

158
00:13:11,999 --> 00:13:13,542
I heard you're coming back to Motto.

159
00:13:13,626 --> 00:13:15,711
I look forward
to your glorious return home, sir.

160
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:29,850
Why are you here in the dead of night
when you're unwell?

161
00:13:37,107 --> 00:13:38,150
Well…

162
00:13:38,234 --> 00:13:40,569
I was out all day long.

163
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:42,488
How was business?

164
00:13:42,571 --> 00:13:44,740
Did you handle everything?

165
00:13:44,823 --> 00:13:45,991
What are you on about?

166
00:13:46,075 --> 00:13:50,371
Did you lie about being unwell
to go off and see your ex-girlfriend?

167
00:13:52,998 --> 00:13:54,416
You're a psychic.

168
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:55,584
What?

169
00:13:56,961 --> 00:13:57,962
Nothing.

170
00:14:02,883 --> 00:14:03,842
Take this with you.

171
00:14:09,014 --> 00:14:10,057
What is it?

172
00:14:14,478 --> 00:14:15,604
You said you're not feeling well.

173
00:14:16,689 --> 00:14:18,941
It's mung bean porridge.
Eat it if you want.

174
00:14:23,696 --> 00:14:25,406
Are you very unwell?

175
00:14:40,713 --> 00:14:41,672
Hey.

176
00:14:43,841 --> 00:14:44,758
You know…

177
00:14:46,468 --> 00:14:47,344
What?

178
00:14:48,637 --> 00:14:50,055
What is it?

179
00:14:53,225 --> 00:14:54,184
Never mind.

180
00:14:55,185 --> 00:14:57,479
It's not important. It can wait.

181
00:14:58,397 --> 00:14:59,565
You're being silly.

182
00:15:01,108 --> 00:15:02,568
Go and get some sleep.

183
00:15:28,218 --> 00:15:31,388
I didn't slack off
because I didn't know how.

184
00:15:34,016 --> 00:15:35,392
Sorry.

185
00:15:35,476 --> 00:15:38,020
I had a sense of responsibility!

186
00:15:40,648 --> 00:15:41,899
You, Choon-seung.

187
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:44,860
Die!

188
00:15:50,199 --> 00:15:52,284
You dare try to take me on?

189
00:15:53,285 --> 00:15:54,620
Die!

190
00:15:58,916 --> 00:16:00,709
Why would you applaud for nothing?

191
00:16:01,377 --> 00:16:03,379
I'm a golfing genius.

192
00:16:15,432 --> 00:16:18,727
They have no idea
who I was trying to help.

193
00:16:19,478 --> 00:16:20,646
I was…

194
00:16:21,814 --> 00:16:23,107
How could they do this to me?

195
00:16:32,866 --> 00:16:34,451
Jin Myung-sook!

196
00:16:34,910 --> 00:16:36,662
DON'T FORGET YOUR BELONGINGS

197
00:16:37,830 --> 00:16:40,874
BEOM-WOO

198
00:16:43,419 --> 00:16:44,878
Oh, come on.

199
00:16:44,962 --> 00:16:47,798
SHIN CHOON-SEUNG

200
00:16:47,881 --> 00:16:49,174
He still won't pick up?

201
00:16:49,717 --> 00:16:51,552
Maybe something did happen to him.

202
00:16:51,635 --> 00:16:52,803
I'm sure he's fine.

203
00:16:53,303 --> 00:16:55,180
I already have a lot on my mind as is.

204
00:16:56,557 --> 00:16:58,767
Excuse me, we need chopsticks.

205
00:16:58,851 --> 00:17:00,519
Chopsticks? I'll bring you some.

206
00:17:14,533 --> 00:17:15,784
Aren't you being too harsh?

207
00:17:17,286 --> 00:17:20,414
There was a reason
I couldn't go in for work.

208
00:17:20,497 --> 00:17:24,293
How many times did I tell you?

209
00:17:25,044 --> 00:17:26,545
There was a reason?

210
00:17:27,129 --> 00:17:32,092
Do you think I go to work
at the restaurant every single day

211
00:17:32,176 --> 00:17:34,845
because I don't have a good reason
to take a single day off?

212
00:17:34,928 --> 00:17:36,805
Do you even know what I had to go through?

213
00:17:36,889 --> 00:17:38,057
What did you say?

214
00:17:38,140 --> 00:17:40,225
You didn't get a word I just said.

215
00:17:41,101 --> 00:17:42,895
Okay, fine. Too bad.

216
00:17:42,978 --> 00:17:46,065
You and I are done as of today.

217
00:17:46,148 --> 00:17:46,982
Yeah, we're done!

218
00:17:47,066 --> 00:17:50,486
South and North Korea can't even reunify,
so how can we get along?

219
00:17:50,569 --> 00:17:52,821
-There's no way.
-Gosh, you're smart, aren't you?

220
00:17:52,905 --> 00:17:56,366
Even a passing dog
in this neighborhood is smart, huh?

221
00:17:56,450 --> 00:17:58,494
-A dog?
-Yeah, a dog!

222
00:17:58,994 --> 00:18:00,746
You dog! Woof, woof!

223
00:18:00,829 --> 00:18:03,082
Oh, so you've decided to bite me now?

224
00:18:03,165 --> 00:18:05,209
Fine, go ahead. Bite me.

225
00:18:05,292 --> 00:18:06,794
-Woof, woof!
-Bite me!

226
00:18:07,795 --> 00:18:09,129
Look, everyone!

227
00:18:09,213 --> 00:18:10,964
Caught both of you in the act!

228
00:18:12,716 --> 00:18:14,468
I was wondering why you both skipped work.

229
00:18:14,551 --> 00:18:15,969
Was it so you could fight?

230
00:18:16,053 --> 00:18:17,930
Did you think I couldn't
or wouldn't go AWOL?

231
00:18:18,013 --> 00:18:19,389
Does this look like we're fighting to you?

232
00:18:19,473 --> 00:18:21,308
I got assaulted!

233
00:18:21,391 --> 00:18:23,477
Are you incapable of realizing
that there's a valid reason

234
00:18:23,560 --> 00:18:24,895
as to why you're being assaulted?

235
00:18:24,978 --> 00:18:26,021
Is your head empty?

236
00:18:26,105 --> 00:18:28,941
-Empty!
-Empty!

237
00:18:29,024 --> 00:18:30,901
-Empty!
-Come on.

238
00:18:30,984 --> 00:18:34,154
-Stop it. Will you help me here?
-You little…

239
00:18:34,238 --> 00:18:37,032
-I don't hear anything.
-Pack your things, everyone!

240
00:18:37,616 --> 00:18:38,784
-What did you say?
-What?

241
00:18:38,867 --> 00:18:40,911
Have you all gone deaf or what?

242
00:18:40,994 --> 00:18:42,579
Pack your stuff tomorrow.

243
00:18:42,663 --> 00:18:44,123
Am I getting fired?

244
00:18:44,206 --> 00:18:45,207
Him?

245
00:18:45,874 --> 00:18:47,167
Let's go on vacation.

246
00:18:47,793 --> 00:18:49,086
-What?
-A vacation?

247
00:18:50,212 --> 00:18:53,715
One's distracted and the other two fight
whenever they meet.

248
00:18:55,467 --> 00:18:59,012
You all worked hard to repay the debt,
and you're burned out.

249
00:18:59,096 --> 00:19:00,514
What does "burned out" mean?

250
00:19:01,390 --> 00:19:03,183
Burned out, like in a fire.

251
00:19:03,267 --> 00:19:04,810
We're all burned and nothing's left.

252
00:19:04,893 --> 00:19:06,562
All burned and nothing's left. Okay.

253
00:19:06,645 --> 00:19:09,857
I feel responsible
for not looking out for my staff.

254
00:19:09,940 --> 00:19:11,608
Let's consider this a vacation

255
00:19:12,109 --> 00:19:14,194
to recharge and bring us together.

256
00:19:14,278 --> 00:19:17,948
Recharging and getting closer,
that's great.

257
00:19:18,031 --> 00:19:19,700
But what about the restaurant?

258
00:19:19,783 --> 00:19:21,785
People are more important
than the restaurant.

259
00:19:21,869 --> 00:19:22,703
That's right.

260
00:19:23,745 --> 00:19:25,873
I'll take that to mean you all agreed.

261
00:19:25,956 --> 00:19:27,166
