ABSOLUTE SILENCE AT ALL TIMES HERE
DO NOT LEAVE ANY FOOD

544
00:38:24,927 --> 00:38:25,928
Okay, I'm first.

545
00:38:26,012 --> 00:38:27,471
Sir, I'm done.

546
00:38:29,932 --> 00:38:31,892
Do I get anything for finishing first?

547
00:38:41,319 --> 00:38:43,946
I finished first. Do you need help?

548
00:38:46,115 --> 00:38:48,826
Are you practicing silence?
Quiet meditating?

549
00:39:11,807 --> 00:39:12,933
Yeon-joo.

550
00:39:13,476 --> 00:39:14,643
Are you asleep?

551
00:39:19,815 --> 00:39:20,900
You asleep?

552
00:39:34,747 --> 00:39:35,998
Why aren't you asleep?

553
00:39:39,377 --> 00:39:41,337
Oh, so you were awake.

554
00:39:42,421 --> 00:39:43,839
Can't sleep?

555
00:39:45,216 --> 00:39:47,218
No, well, I was just…

556
00:39:49,845 --> 00:39:54,475
So about what I was going to say
the other day…

557
00:39:54,558 --> 00:39:56,060
The moon is so bright.

558
00:39:56,644 --> 00:39:57,603
Oh my.

559
00:39:58,771 --> 00:40:00,106
It really is bright.

560
00:40:03,192 --> 00:40:04,193
What were you saying?

561
00:40:09,490 --> 00:40:10,449
Never mind.

562
00:40:12,201 --> 00:40:15,663
There was someone
I really wanted you to meet here.

563
00:40:17,790 --> 00:40:18,791
The head monk?

564
00:40:20,167 --> 00:40:21,335
How did you know?

565
00:40:22,461 --> 00:40:24,046
I could tell right away.

566
00:40:25,297 --> 00:40:27,508
The person you said was like your mother.

567
00:40:28,467 --> 00:40:29,427
Isn't that her?

568
00:40:31,429 --> 00:40:33,347
Yeah, my mom.

569
00:40:34,515 --> 00:40:36,058
She's not like my mom.

570
00:40:37,268 --> 00:40:38,602
She is my mom.

571
00:41:06,881 --> 00:41:09,550
I'M SORRY. PLEASE TAKE HER IN.

572
00:41:17,516 --> 00:41:18,934
Oh dear.

573
00:41:22,730 --> 00:41:23,772
My gosh.

574
00:41:32,490 --> 00:41:33,616
I was so happy here

575
00:41:35,159 --> 00:41:37,870
that I never thought of
or missed my real mom.

576
00:42:00,976 --> 00:42:03,729
The monks were my aunts and uncles.

577
00:42:09,109 --> 00:42:10,611
And the head monk was my mom.

578
00:42:17,243 --> 00:42:18,702
Can we add the potatoes now?

579
00:42:18,786 --> 00:42:20,371
We sure can.

580
00:42:28,045 --> 00:42:30,339
She always cooked me tasty food,

581
00:42:30,422 --> 00:42:32,466
saying my heart should never get hungry.

582
00:42:39,390 --> 00:42:40,224
There.

583
00:42:40,307 --> 00:42:41,684
-Here.
-Yes.

584
00:42:43,185 --> 00:42:44,853
-One.
-Okay.

585
00:42:47,064 --> 00:42:48,857
-Two.
-That's it.

586
00:42:52,361 --> 00:42:57,366
Thanks to the food I cooked with Mom
and everything she taught me to make,

587
00:42:58,576 --> 00:43:00,911
I fell in love with cooking.

588
00:43:03,330 --> 00:43:04,665
Oh, it's vegetables with rice.

589
00:43:06,792 --> 00:43:08,919
SILENCE

590
00:43:09,920 --> 00:43:11,505
Thank you for the food!

591
00:43:13,465 --> 00:43:16,385
Back then, I was

592
00:43:17,219 --> 00:43:18,554
just so happy.

593
00:43:19,221 --> 00:43:20,598
Mom!

594
00:43:20,681 --> 00:43:22,474
-Hey.
-I'm back.

595
00:43:22,558 --> 00:43:24,727
-You're back.
-Be careful.

596
00:43:26,103 --> 00:43:27,605
I'll do it, Auntie.

597
00:43:27,688 --> 00:43:28,772
-What? No.
-Let me.

598
00:43:28,856 --> 00:43:31,692
-It's fine. I'll do it.
-Let me do the rest.

599
00:43:31,775 --> 00:43:34,820
You just got back from school. Goodness.

600
00:43:35,571 --> 00:43:36,488
Did you study hard?

601
00:43:36,572 --> 00:43:39,199
-Yes, but I'm hungry.
-What do you want to eat?

602
00:43:41,702 --> 00:43:43,537
I got accepted to CIA,

603
00:43:44,747 --> 00:43:46,081
and I cried so much

604
00:43:47,041 --> 00:43:48,500
the day I left this place.

605
00:43:49,209 --> 00:43:50,127
Yeon-joo.

606
00:43:53,464 --> 00:43:54,381
Auntie.

607
00:43:57,343 --> 00:44:00,012
Be well and healthy in the US, okay?

608
00:44:14,652 --> 00:44:16,820
It's all okay.

609
00:44:19,073 --> 00:44:20,199
It's okay.

610
00:44:20,282 --> 00:44:21,325
Thank you.

611
00:44:22,076 --> 00:44:23,243
It's okay.

612
00:44:32,002 --> 00:44:34,755
They're people who cared for me every day.

613
00:44:35,339 --> 00:44:36,340
To me,

614
00:44:37,508 --> 00:44:39,468
they're all so special.

615
00:44:40,511 --> 00:44:41,929
Especially my mom.

616
00:44:44,473 --> 00:44:46,684
That's why I wanted you to meet her.

617
00:44:51,355 --> 00:44:54,983
It's okay. We can come back again.

618
00:44:55,567 --> 00:44:56,527
Of course.

619
00:44:57,444 --> 00:44:58,654
We can come back again.

620
00:44:59,530 --> 00:45:01,281
It feels like
I'm always the one doing the talking.

621
00:45:02,408 --> 00:45:03,534
What?

622
00:45:07,579 --> 00:45:09,206
I want to hear your story too.

623
00:45:12,209 --> 00:45:13,794
The cabbage kimchi.

624
00:45:14,878 --> 00:45:16,255
What's the story behind that?

625
00:45:16,755 --> 00:45:18,215
Is it what your mom made for you?

626
00:45:23,220 --> 00:45:26,306
You were so out of it while eating it
when you first came to the restaurant.

627
00:45:35,107 --> 00:45:36,108
No.

628
00:45:37,151 --> 00:45:39,903
It's not what my mom made.

629
00:45:41,822 --> 00:45:44,741
It's what my grandma made.

630
00:45:44,825 --> 00:45:46,118
I see.

631
00:45:47,828 --> 00:45:49,997
You don't have to tell me
if you don't want to.

632
00:45:51,874 --> 00:45:53,584
You can tell me some other time.

633
00:45:59,506 --> 00:46:00,924
The thing is…

634
00:46:02,801 --> 00:46:06,638
It's really hard to tell.

635
00:46:16,899 --> 00:46:18,984
HANSANG

636
00:46:19,067 --> 00:46:21,653
The Diamant inspectors
visited Motto yesterday,

637
00:46:21,737 --> 00:46:23,489
