was apparently very positive.

638
00:46:30,829 --> 00:46:32,164
You can go.

639
00:46:43,550 --> 00:46:44,384
HAN BEOM-WOO

640
00:46:44,468 --> 00:46:46,094
I'M NOT GOING BACK TO MOTTO

641
00:46:46,178 --> 00:46:48,514
I DON'T NEED HANSANG
OR TO BE THE SUCCESSOR ANYMORE

642
00:47:03,153 --> 00:47:04,071
Hello?

643
00:47:08,367 --> 00:47:10,327
Oh, I'm sorry.

644
00:47:10,410 --> 00:47:12,079
I bought my phone recently.

645
00:47:12,162 --> 00:47:13,789
Call me again in two years.

646
00:47:14,998 --> 00:47:17,543
Damn it.
Shouldn't they have called by now?

647
00:47:19,211 --> 00:47:20,712
Do you think we failed?

648
00:47:20,796 --> 00:47:23,757
Let's wait a bit more. Korea and the US
have different time zones.

649
00:47:23,840 --> 00:47:24,967
Don't you mean France?

650
00:47:25,676 --> 00:47:28,303
-It's the Diamant Guide.
-I know, okay? I know.

651
00:47:31,056 --> 00:47:32,015
Wait.

652
00:47:38,647 --> 00:47:39,898
Hello?

653
00:47:42,025 --> 00:47:44,361
Hello. How are you?

654
00:47:46,530 --> 00:47:47,364
Oh, is that so?

655
00:47:48,740 --> 00:47:51,159
Okay, thank you. Goodbye.

656
00:47:55,622 --> 00:47:56,623
What did they say?

657
00:47:58,500 --> 00:47:59,501
Well?

658
00:48:01,295 --> 00:48:02,921
The Diamant Guide gave three stars

659
00:48:03,547 --> 00:48:06,133
to just one restaurant in Korea.

660
00:48:14,850 --> 00:48:15,684
Three stars!

661
00:48:15,767 --> 00:48:17,311
Three stars!

662
00:48:17,394 --> 00:48:20,063
-Three stars!
-Three stars!

663
00:48:20,147 --> 00:48:21,023
Cheers!

664
00:48:40,250 --> 00:48:42,919
Did you have a peaceful stay?

665
00:48:44,004 --> 00:48:47,007
Everyone in the world commits wrongs.

666
00:48:48,300 --> 00:48:51,511
Another word we use
for foolishness is "ignorance."

667
00:48:52,346 --> 00:48:56,224
It means those who don't know
the truth of things are in the dark.

668
00:48:57,392 --> 00:48:59,394
I hope that
when you return to your places,

669
00:49:00,187 --> 00:49:02,856
you each find your truth.

670
00:49:07,569 --> 00:49:08,904
He doesn't need it, my ass.

671
00:49:09,571 --> 00:49:11,490
Han Beom-woo, you dare deceive me?

672
00:49:58,245 --> 00:49:59,955
We're back.

673
00:50:00,038 --> 00:50:01,998
Well done, everyone.

674
00:50:02,082 --> 00:50:04,000
Get home safely,
and I'll see you tomorrow.

675
00:50:04,084 --> 00:50:05,377
-See you.
-Bye.

676
00:50:09,214 --> 00:50:11,466
What are you doing?
I'll drive you to the inn.

677
00:50:13,135 --> 00:50:14,219
Hey, Choon-seung.

678
00:50:14,302 --> 00:50:18,140
I have to discuss something with Chef Mo.

679
00:50:18,223 --> 00:50:21,143
You want to work right after a vacation?
Just get back in.

680
00:50:22,352 --> 00:50:24,312
Take care of my stuff for me.

681
00:50:24,396 --> 00:50:26,356
-Okay?
-I said I'd drop you off. Get in!

682
00:50:27,274 --> 00:50:29,359
Just go. Start driving.

683
00:51:13,153 --> 00:51:14,070
You know…

684
00:51:17,574 --> 00:51:19,284
I've changed a lot since I came here.

685
00:51:22,412 --> 00:51:26,041
I met you, Myung-sook, and Choon-seung

686
00:51:26,875 --> 00:51:28,835
and realized
we don't go through life alone.

687
00:51:32,380 --> 00:51:33,298
And…

688
00:51:34,758 --> 00:51:37,010
I realized that sincerity
means more than money…

689
00:51:40,889 --> 00:51:42,557
and that people are more important.

690
00:51:44,684 --> 00:51:45,769
I learned all those things…

691
00:51:48,605 --> 00:51:50,190
from you, Yeon-joo.

692
00:51:55,570 --> 00:51:58,281
That's why…

693
00:52:01,117 --> 00:52:02,327
there's something

694
00:52:03,578 --> 00:52:05,622
I have to say today.

695
00:52:41,616 --> 00:52:42,659
Yeon-joo.

696
00:52:51,877 --> 00:52:52,794
You're here.

697
00:52:56,256 --> 00:52:57,507
I came out of curiosity.

698
00:52:58,550 --> 00:53:00,468
To see if you were done
shutting things down.

699
00:53:01,469 --> 00:53:02,387
Shutting down?

700
00:53:06,057 --> 00:53:08,560
No, well, you see…

701
00:53:08,643 --> 00:53:10,270
I guess the chef doesn't know

702
00:53:11,021 --> 00:53:15,525
why you came here
and why you're working here.

703
00:53:17,110 --> 00:53:18,486
Listen, Chef.

704
00:53:18,570 --> 00:53:19,696
Han Beom-woo's actually--

705
00:53:19,779 --> 00:53:20,822
Han Sun-woo!

706
00:53:31,416 --> 00:53:32,959
You tell me yourself.

707
00:53:34,085 --> 00:53:35,045
What's he saying?

708
00:53:45,847 --> 00:53:46,681
At…

709
00:53:50,060 --> 00:53:51,645
At first…

710
00:53:53,688 --> 00:53:54,773
At first…

711
00:53:56,650 --> 00:53:59,945
I was going to take the recipes
once I took over the restaurant

712
00:54:01,905 --> 00:54:03,073
and shut it down.

713
00:54:03,156 --> 00:54:04,240
At first.

714
00:54:07,953 --> 00:54:09,287
You were going to take my recipes…

715
00:54:12,624 --> 00:54:13,750
and shut down my restaurant?

716
00:54:19,631 --> 00:54:22,425
That was the plan at first.

717
00:54:22,509 --> 00:54:23,426
"At first"?

718
00:54:24,427 --> 00:54:27,013
You already sold a dish
made with the recipe you stole from here.

719
00:54:28,515 --> 00:54:30,225
Wild pine mushroom seopsanjeok.

720
00:54:30,308 --> 00:54:32,018
That's your recipe, isn't it?

721
00:54:34,062 --> 00:54:37,148
Your restaurant, Motto,
got three stars with that dish.

722
00:54:37,983 --> 00:54:38,900
Congratulations.

723
00:54:47,200 --> 00:54:48,243
Please.

724
00:54:53,790 --> 00:54:54,958
Let me tell her.

725
00:54:57,711 --> 00:54:58,753
Is it true?

726
00:55:02,882 --> 00:55:03,800
Is it?

727
00:55:07,137 --> 00:55:08,138
Is it?

728
00:55:22,902 --> 00:55:23,862
Yeah.

729
00:55:45,091 --> 00:55:47,052
I meant to tell you the truth sooner.

730
00:55:47,135 --> 00:55:48,303
The truth?

731
00:55:48,887 --> 00:55:50,096
When?

732
00:55:50,722 --> 00:55:52,057
When were you going to tell me?

733
00:55:53,850 --> 00:55:55,935
After all the lying and stealing,

734
00:55:56,019 --> 00:55:57,479
now you tell the truth?

735
00:55:57,562 --> 00:55:59,355
Will you hear me out?

736
00:55:59,439 --> 00:56:00,315
How…

737
00:56:03,943 --> 00:56:04,986
How…

738
00:56:08,281 --> 00:56:12,160
How could you toy with my sincerity?

739
00:56:17,832 --> 00:56:18,833
Yeon-joo.

740
00:56:19,417 --> 00:56:20,293
Get out.

741
00:56:22,712 --> 00:56:23,630
Get out.

742
00:56:26,883 --> 00:56:27,759
Please leave.

743
00:56:32,555 --> 00:56:33,598
Please.

744
00:57:18,226 --> 00:57:19,978
JUNGJAE

745
00:57:32,365 --> 00:57:33,324
Just…

746
00:57:36,911 --> 00:57:38,121
Just let me go.

747
00:57:45,128 --> 00:57:46,838
Why don't you beat me up this time?

748
00:57:48,423 --> 00:57:49,299
Come on.

749
00:57:53,678 --> 00:57:56,598
If only you hadn't lied
and said you didn't need Hansang,

750
00:57:57,682 --> 00:57:59,601
I wouldn't have gone this far!

751
00:58:06,858 --> 00:58:08,526
Goddammit.

752
00:58:28,796 --> 00:58:30,048
I never got to tell you.

753
00:58:32,467 --> 00:58:33,510
I'm sorry.

754
00:59:14,634 --> 00:59:16,261
TASTEFULLY YOURS

755
00:59:16,344 --> 00:59:19,305
I'm sorry, but we need to
close the restaurant for a while.

756
00:59:19,806 --> 00:59:22,267
I don't know what to do.

757
00:59:22,350 --> 00:59:24,644
He's a con man. He's a fraud!

758
00:59:24,727 --> 00:59:27,981
I'm sorry this is all I know to do.

759
00:59:28,064 --> 00:59:30,942
I wonder if I was the only one
who was sincere.

760
00:59:31,025 --> 00:59:32,402
I'll see to it that the chef girl

761
00:59:32,485 --> 00:59:35,613
won't be able to set foot
in this industry.

762
00:59:36,114 --> 00:59:38,324
Jungjae might disappear.

763
00:59:38,408 --> 00:59:40,743
Why would
a perfectly fine restaurant disappear?

